<topic id="docbook-2-pfd-transform">
  <title>DocBook to PDF Transformation</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>DocBook to PDF</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DocBook to PDF transformation</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> includes a built-in transformation scenario that is designed to
      convert DocBook content to PDF.</p>
    <p>To convert a DocBook document to PDF, follow these steps:<ol>
        <li>Use one of the following two methods to begin the transformation process:<ul>
            <li>To apply the transformation scenario to a newly opened file, use the
                  <uicontrol><image href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png" id="image_csb_4yv_sr"/>Apply
                Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
                  conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_t_shortcut"
                  product="author developer editor"/></uicontrol><uicontrol><shortcut
                  conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tt_shortcut"
                  product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from
              the toolbar or the <menucascade product="author developer editor">
                <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
                <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol>
              </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
                >XML</uicontrol> menu.</li>
            <li>To customize the transformation or change the scenario that is associated with the
              document, use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
                  id="image_hcv_gwv_sr"/>Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
                  conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_c_shortcut"
                  product="author developer editor"/></uicontrol><uicontrol><shortcut
                  conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
                  product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from
              the toolbar or the <menucascade product="author developer editor">
                <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
                <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol>
              </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
                >XML</uicontrol> menu.</li>
          </ul></li>
        <li>Select the <uicontrol>DocBook PDF</uicontrol> transformation scenario in the
            <uicontrol>DocBook 4</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>DocBook 5</uicontrol> section.</li>
        <li>Click the <uicontrol>Apply associated</uicontrol> button to run the transformation.</li>
      </ol></p>
    <p>For information about customizing the PDF output for DocBook content, see <xref
        href="docbook-pdf-output-customization.dita#docbook-pdf-output-customization"/>.</p>
  </body>
